name: yarn-api-client
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "yarn-api-client" %}
{% set version = "0.3.6" %}
{% set sha256 = "ff0e3b2e74225461190031d23b55a353b02dfb045923ad04e638ebc8c2feaf36" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed --no-cache-dir -vvv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip

  run:
    - python
    - requests >=2.7,<3.0
    - requests-kerberos

test:
  imports:
    - yarn_api_client

  commands:
    - python -m yarn_api_client --help
    - python -c "from yarn_api_client import ApplicationMaster, HistoryServer, NodeManager, ResourceManager"

about:
  home: https://python-client-for-hadoop-yarn-api.readthedocs.io/en/latest/
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Python client for Hadoop® YARN API
  doc_url: https://python-client-for-hadoop-yarn-api.readthedocs.io/en/latest/
  dev_url: https://github.com/toidi/hadoop-yarn-api-python-client.git

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - ericdill
    - lresende
